  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of this study is to evaluate the efficacy of a specialized exclusive
      breastfeeding education and support program targeting obese, pregnant, low-income women in
      Hartford, CT. Specifically, the investigators will evaluate the impact of the intervention on
      exclusive and partial breastfeeding rates at birth, 1, 3 and 6 months pp. Secondary aims of
      this study are: a) to characterize postpartum weight loss patterns and blood pressure values
      of obese women, by study group; and b) to evaluate potential differences in infant morbidity
      (diarrhea, otitis media and rehospitalization), by study group.
    </textblock>
